cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the security and reliability of wireless sensor networks, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS), systems and control (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on data survivability and the use of an epidemic-domain inspired approach suggest that cs.CR and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.SY, and cs.IT.
